SIMPLE: figured
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Figured
<hw>Fig"ured</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Adorned
with figures; marked with figures; <as>as, <ex>figured</ex>
muslin</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not literal; figurative.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Locke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Free and florid;
<as>as, a <ex>figured</ex> descant</as>. See <er>Figurate</er>, 3.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>Indicated or noted by figures.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Figured bass</b></col>. <cd>See <cref>Continued
bass</cref>, under <er>Continued</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Figurehead</ent>⟦br⟧
